lation of both rhetoric and hermeneutics, this collection is sure to serve as a benchmark for years to come.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aHermeneuticsxHistoryy20th century. 0aInterpretation (Philosophy). 0aRhetoricxHistoryxPhilosophyy20th century. 0aRhetoricxPhilosophyxHistoryy20th century. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Epistemology.2bisacsh1 aAltieri, Charles, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBruns, Gerald L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCopeland, Rita, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGadamer, Hans-Georg, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGarver, Eugene, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHyde, Michael. J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJost, Walter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKahn, Victoria, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLeff, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLevy, Jerrold E., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aMailloux, Steven, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMarshall, Donald G., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOlmsted, Wendy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPalmer, Richard E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRehg, William, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRicoeur, Paul, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchrag, Calvin O., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aScult, Allen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov